[[div class="blockquote"]]
**Interviewer:** Adrian Boehm
**Interviewee:** Michael Smith [[footnote]] A former terrorist and member of LTO-6543-Tesla "Church of the Broken God", in coalition custody since the start of the offensive operations against remnants of LTO-6543-Tesla in the United Kingdom[[/footnote]]
**Foreword:** The following interview was conducted following a failed infiltration by a member of KTO-7890-Valentinus by the name of Eldar Abdullayev. The member attempted to breach into a GOC facility, claiming to be looking to negotiate an alliance between KTO-7890-Valentinus and the Global Occult Coalition. The hostile self-terminated following apprehension and attempts at advanced interrogation. A tattoo on his body, containing a spiral symbols, was found to match a symbol labelled a "forbidden sigil" in the Maxwellist Book of Horrors, a piece of scripture recovered from an LTO-6543-Tesla member's hard drive.

-----
//[BEGIN LOG]//

//[Adrian Boehm enters the interrogation room, carrying a glass of water and a file of documents. Michael Smith is seen staring at a wall, motionless]//

**Adrian Boehm:** Good evening, Mr. Smith! It's been a while since we've last talk, hasn't it?

//[Smith audibly sighs]//

**Michael Smith:** What do you want from me again?

**Adrian Boehm:** Oh, just a friendly chat, really. I was actually curious how-

**Michael Smith:** Specifics.

//[Boehm places the file on the table and opens it on the first page, showing the photo of the deceased body of Eldar Abdullayev]//

**Adrian Boehm:** Very well. This symbol, we've seen it in your scripture. Can you tell us what it means? We've had this man approach us, claim he was from..."Nälkä for a New Millenium", then proceed to kill himself when we tried to extract information from him. Really strange man, I have to say.

//[Smith looks at the file, then at Boehm. He is seen to be visibly agitated. He shakes his head]//

**Michael Smith:** No, you...you don't know what you are dealing with!

**Adrian Boehm:** Then please, enlighten us.

**Michael Smith:** These...heathens, they are flesh worshippers. Our church has upheld our sacred duty of weeding them out, and when you declared war on us, you took their side! MEKHANE, please give me the stren-

**Adrian Boehm:** I assure you, we didn't take anyone's side. But that is neither here nor there. Are you saying they are a religious movement, like yours? How many are there of them?

**Michael Smith:** I don't know, a few hundred. And no, they are something else. They follow the god of the Flesh, they want to bring destruction to this world and recreate it in its image. We have to stop them! You have to-

**Adrian Boehm:** Alright, thank you, Mr. Smith. I believe that is all I needed to know. I assure you, we'll use this knowledge accordingly

//[END LOG]//
[[/div]]

