[[div class="blockquote"]]
The following document is a complete list of all attacks[[footnote]] As of 22/08/2022[[/footnote]] by KTO-7890-Valentinus which have resulted in one or more Coalition casualties. A list of casualties has been attached at the end of each file.
[[tabview]]
[[tab 05/02/2021]]
Shortly following interview AE-5935, the PNEUMA Division-Siberian Command was informed of a group of villages housing a group of anomalous humanoids. At that time, the Coalition was not yet aware of KTO-7890-Valentinus. A plan was drafted to relocate the villagers into CT-1361-Carter. A negotiator was sent on 04/02/2021 to inform the community of the plan and establish a timeline for the evacuation. Shortly following their arrival, an argument broke out. A sample of the conversation's transcript can be viewed below.

> **Negotiator:** I am telling you, there is nothing I ca-
>
> **Unidentified female:** Tsars didn't exile us, Khrushchev didn't exile us, and who are you now?
>
> **Negotiator:** Ma'am, I am sorry-
>
> **Unidentified male:** One more word and I will pull your guts out of your mouth, you goat[[footnote]] Common Russian insult[[/footnote]]!

Following this interaction, the negotiator exited the village, being unable to establish a relation with neither the locals nor find a community leader. As they were leaving, contact with them was suddenly lost. A surveillance drone was sent to the village the next day, spotting a group of men burying a bloody corpse. Following this attack, the villages were designated as hostile actors and swiftly neutralized using [https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/collective-punishment incendiary weapons].
[[/tab]]
[[tab 19/12/2021]]

**UNCONFIRMED INCIDENT**

[[include :scp-wiki:component:image-block
| name= https://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/art:goc-unit-insignia/721-Lazy-Wolf.png
| caption= The insignia of Assessment Team 721 "Lazy Wolf"
| width=200px]]

In the months leading to the incident, 4 members of Assessment Team 721 "Lazy Wolf" were dispatched to UTE-5936-Moor "La Rue Macabre"[[footnote]] A pocket dimension composed of a single settlement and an marshland of undetermined size. Suspected to house multiple Threat Entities[[/footnote]]. During their investigation, the team was able to uncover a [https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/the-mekhanics-of-la-rue-part-one previously unknown sect of LTO-6543-Tesla], as well as religious group calling themselves "Äkum'nälkä". Members of the sect appeared to have vacated UTE-5936-Moor "La Rue Macabre" in the weeks prior to the team's arrival. It is now suspected that the cult was a regional branch of KTO-7890-Valentinus.

All contact with the team was suddenly lost on 19/12/2021, leading to an investigation by members of Assessment Team 712 "Dispatchers". Attempts were made to interview inhabitants of UTE-5936-Moor under the guise of anomalous journalism. All interviewed claimed the team was killed by alligators while venturing into the swamp surrounding the town [[footnote]] The existence of a civilization of anthropomorphic alligators called "Gatormen" has been rumoured to exist in the swamp compromising most of the pocket dimension[[/footnote]]. The team's base of operations was found to have been demolished. No bodies have been recovered.

[[/tab]]
[[tab 24/02/2022]]

Daniel Acart, age 68, served as Senior Officer of the PHYSICS Division's Eastern European command. On 24/02/2022, he was visiting members of his family when he was kidnapped by two assailants, identified as members of KTO-7890-Valentinus. The timeline of the kidnapping can be viewed below.

> **2043:** Senior Officer Acart is seen exiting the apartment belonging to his daughter, Angela Acart. He appears to be agitated. Statements from Angela Acart indicate the two had an argument regarding her father's smoking habits.
>
> **2045:** A neighborhood camera records Senior Officer Acart searching through his coat, before shaking his head and looking around the area. He proceeds out of the frame
>
> **2051:** The camera of a nearby convinience store records Senior Officer Acart entering it, followed by two men wearing black hoodies. Senior Officer Acart purchases a pack of cigarettes.
>
> **2052:** One of the men trips towards Senior Officer Acart, making both of them fall down. He is seen apologizing, before helping him up. During questioning, the cashier reported that the man was squeezing Senior Officer Acart's right hand "like a lemon".
>
> **2053:** Senior Officer Acart exits the store. One of the men reaches for a product on the shelves, revealing a tattoo on his hand resembling a sigil commonly used by KTO-7890-Valentinus
>
> **2056:** The two men exit the store, having purchased a single beer and a bag of chips using cash. They start walking towards Senior Officer Acart, who is attempting to light a cigarette. He is visibly struggling, with his right hand shaking.
>
> **2108:**  Senior Officer Acart is briefly recorded by a street camera as he walks backwards, holding a pistol with his left hand[[footnote]] Senior Officer Acart was right-handed[[/footnote]]. He is seen walking with a visible limp. His mouth is open, likely yelling something
>
> **2110:** The sound of gunshots is recorded by a local civillian after they heard sounds of commotion outside their window. It is followed by the sound of a car rapidly accelerating.
>
> **2011** A black van is recorded rapidly driving away from the area towards which Senior Officer Acart was last seen walking. The license plate of the vehicle could not be discerned.

The fate of Daniel Acart is currently unknown. No ransom demands have been made, nor has a body been found.

[[/tab]]
[[tab 13/06/2022]]

Following the previous incident, KTO-7890-Valentinus had been raised to a collective threat level of 3, designating all its operatives and associated Parathreats and immediate dangers to normalcy. Coalition Outpost #43, staffed primarily by members of the PNEUMA and PTOLEMY divisions, was tasked with research regarding the Threat Organization and findings possible ways of infiltration. Operation Irenaeus was founded shortly after, with the goal of infiltration and eventual destruction of the Threat Organization.

In the week leading up to the incident, janitorial personnel reported the smell of rotting flesh, in addition to hearing chanting coming from locked rooms during the night shifts. At the same time, multiple other staff members were spotted with injuries they were unable to explain, including missing small chunks of skin and muscle tissue. All injuries were found to be stitched or otherwise showed signs of tending to shortly after they were sustained.

The following message was received by the Regional Coalition Headquarters on 13/06/2022 at 22:57.

> Can anyone hear me? My name's Maria //[5 second pause]// Maria Roth. Field agent, detective... We need assistance. A strike team at the very least! Oh, right... We were called for the meeting, one of the team leaders said they had a breakthrough, and then...and then everything went to shit. I enter and one of the guards were just... Flayed out on the table, his guts are still moving. There were these symbols, they must be from Valentinus, drawn across the floors and walls showing eyes and snakes and... A few of us were torn apart right there and then. We started shooting that thing and it stopped moving, but there were more of them. Don't think they were people... Fuck, they infiltrated us, [https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-2075 and we didn't even know]... I think the command's dead. I've locked myself in here, but I heard some squeaks coming from the vents. Fuck... Please send someone, I don't know how many are still alive out there.

The site was stormed by Strike Team-0984 "Cleaning Crew" half an hour later. The Strike Team suffered 10 casualities, including 7 dead. Out of 83 personnel present at the site during the attack, only 24 survived, 9 of them seriously injured. Most electronics were found to be destroyed beyond recovery, leading to the destruction of the majority of data on KTO-7890-Valentinus that had not been saved to an external server.

[[/tab]]
[[tab 20/08/2022]]

Starting on 09/08/2022, reports of fur-covered, humanoid entities surfaced, centered around the forests of the Aisne Department, France. Rumours of lycanthropic entities have been previously spread around the area, beginning shortly after the end of the First World War. While investigation into the area had been considered in the past, the lack of evidence pointing towards parathreats in the area, in addition to shortage of resources, led to proposals for any such operations being dismissed.

After multiple photos and recordings of unidentified figures have emerged from the area, the 5 person Strike Team-0384 "Good Boys" was sent to terminate or apprehend any lycanthropic entities present.

> //[BEGIN LOG]//
>
> **"Crow":** Mission update, we have made our way 5 kilometers into the forest. No signs of parathreats so far, only mundane animal tracks. How's the drone looking, Badger?
>
> **"Badger":** No unusual heat signatures, save for us, either.
>
> **"Crow":** Copy that.
>
> **"Peacock":** Got somethin', chief. Weird symbols, carved on the tree. Anyone got the scanner?
>
> //[Agent "Grasshopper" approaches Agent "Peacock", carrying a scanner with built in access to the Global Occult Coalition Parathreat Database. A circle containing a humanoid skull with a single eye and husks is seen carved into an overturned log]//
>
> **"Grasshopper":** One moment, it need a second to-oh. Crow, I think you want to see this
>
> //[Agent "Crow" approaches the two team mebers and look at the scanning device]//
>
> **"Crow":** Valentinus...but what do they have to do with Lycanthropes? Command, do you copy? We have...possibly located traces of a Threat Organization. We're not sure if they are responsible for the
>
> **"Badger":** Two humanoid figures, to our north, rapidly approaching!
>
> //[The team switches the safety on their firearms off and looks in the direction of the approaching humanoids. Two figures are seen in the distance, running in between trees]//
>
> **"Crow":** Don't step any closer! Hands up, or we will shoot!
>
> //[The team repeatedly shouts it into the treeline, both in French and English, eliciting no response. Three shots are fired in the air by Agent Crow.]//
>
> **"Badger":** Two more to our south now!
>
> **"Grasshoper":** Where the fuck are they coming fro-
>
> //[The team falls silent for a moment as sound of leaves falling and wood breaking can be heard. The ground under Agent Peacock collapses, resulting in him falling into a previously disguised tunnel. The sound of rapidly approaching footsteps is heard from his microphone]//
>
> **"Peacock":** What...no, n-no, no!
>
> //[Sounds of growling, gunshots and tearing flesh are heard coming from the tunnel as Agent Crow approaches it. His camera is able to record Agent Peacock's hands as he is dragged into the tunnel by an unseen assailant]//
>
> **"Crow":** Command! We're requesting Immediate exfil. Unknown number of Parathreats in the area, at least 4. Team, open fire!
>
> //[As the humanoids approach, all members of the team fire towards them, scoring multiple direct hits on their bodies. They are able to be seen more clearly at this point, resembling post-transformation lycanthropes. Unusual for humans effected with lycanthropy, the silver bullets the team is firing seem to be doing little damage to their bodies, their wounds mending shortly after being injured]//
>
> **Unidentified Humanoid:** Weak, weak, weak!
>
> //[The humanoids circle around the team, getting closer every few seconds. Agent Crow's body camera records 8 visible at one time. The drone feed shows a group of over a dozen making its way towards the team]//
>
> **"Crow":** Stand your ground! They want us to separate!
>
> //[As Agent Crow yells, Agent Grosshopper looks towards him, allowing for a humanoid to pounce on his back. It begins biting at his shoulder, then neck. Agent Badger and Agent Crow fire at it, neutralizing it. Two humanoids approach them at this time, slashing across Agent Badger's face with its claws once before falling onto the ground. As its wounds start mending, the injured agent shoots it once in the head]//
>
> **"Badger":** Fucking hell...at least it didn't bite me-
>
> **"Crow:"** Doesn't matter, we've got to!
>
> //[The two surviving members launch grenades from under their rifle's barrels, causing the humanoids to scatter back. As no one is piloting the drone at this point, the feed only shows a tree on which it focused prior to the attack. Agents Crow and Badger are able to reach a nearby road, at which point the humanoids cease chasing them]//
>
> //[END LOG]//
>

Agent Badger has since made a full recovery. The families of the deceased agents have been compensated.

[[/tab]]
[[/tabview]]


