{{Opening ##blue|Battle_Report_23/10/2022.pto##...}}
[[/div]]
[[/=]]

[[div class="blockquote"]]

I have been asked to provide a complete report on the latest battle against KTO-7890-Valentinus. Being the commanding officer of the Strike Team, I trust myself much more than my men to give you the unbiased facts of what had happened.

We arrived at entrance of the settlement at circa 1740, based on the intelligence provided from us by the local agents. The "Seŭlga", as that particular group of Valentinus members called themselves, had not erected any notable defenses at the entrance to their settlement. There were three, large wooden doors in total. As we later learned, all led to different structures in the community. Approaching them led to all of our electronic equipment shutting down, as we were previously informed would happen. Two squads stayed behind, guarding the side entrances, while we set up explosives and prepared to breach through the middle.

On the other side of the door we found a sort of plaza, devoid of life. Multiple stone structures were suddenly in our view, as well as a large complex of wooden, stone and organic buildings. We presume the  latter to be some sort of temple. At first, there was no sight of hostiles or autonomous biological material.

That is, until we made our way about halfway into it. Suddenly, we found ourselves under fire, both from bolt-action rifles, as well as arrows. One even embedded itself in my armour, though it thankfully stopped short of piercing my skin. Our team fell back, using trees and stone shrines strewn across the settlement as cover. We began to engage the enemy, who were shootings at us from the roofs.

We lost three men during the exchange. One was hit with an arrow to his thigh. Our medic was able to drag him into cover, but by that time, I saw him leaking out of the hole in his suit. No, I am not talking about just blood. He was moving for a while, too. Another one was fatally wounded while running between cover, while the last got shot when we were exchanging fire. Another got wounded, right in the thigh. This all lasted for around 4 minutes, then we stopped hearing return fire. Judging by how there was blood seeping down from at least one of the roofs, all the hostiles appeared to be either dead, injured or have fallen back.

It is at this point that we split into two teams. One went over to the houses to finish up whoever was left, the other to secure the temple. I was leading the second. Me and ten of my men made our way up the stairs, only to notice this...small crowd, gathered near a door. Well, door isn't a good name for it. It looked like a closed maw, covered in some clear, slimy material. The crowd was mostly adolescents, save for a few old women and men. There were two white men, really standing out from the rest. We fired and shot the one closest, right in his stomach. Some of the kids turned to us and yelled something. Child soldiers, clearly. Oh, and the injured one yelled something to the other. "Volya!", I believe.

Must have been a signal to attack, as right after, three men jump out of the bushes, right behind us. Spears in hand, yelling battle cries. All had those long, white spears with them. Probably made of bone, judging by what we know of these savages. One of my men was stabbed, other got hit over his head but the helmet saved him. The one they got started twitching and bleeding all over. We knew we couldn't do much for him. We neutralized all three, then quickly swept the area to confirm that none other remained. Once we were sure, we approached the temple again.

There wasn't anyone left near the maw by that time. We opted to throw grenades at it, we're still not sure if the damaged anything that was on the other side or not. We weren't able to get it to open during clearing operations, either. In any case, we started sweeping through the temple, after the other boys radioed in to tell us they have neutralized the remaining hostiles outside of. We told them to double check, then join us.

Once we regrouped, we moved through the remaining buildings. There were six of them, all filled with those weird symbols they put around everywhere. Paintings too. Some even had statues. I could recognize Buddha somewhere there, but the rest looked alien. In the literal sense of that word. We encountered only 4 hostiles there, two playing dead on the floor, another with his hands up in the air and trying to feign surrender. We finally reached the last building, at the back of the whole complex.

Inside, it looked more like a house than a place of prayer. A very spartan house, sure, but a house. There was a bed, a gas stove, some kind of shrine, there was even a table. More importantly, there a middle aged man in grey robes, sitting in the center of the structure, cross-legged and just staring at us while we breached inside. He seemed to be meditating, unfazed by the battle outside. I suspect he was a Karcist, or whatever the cultists call their priests. We swiftly neutralized him and saw him hit the ground. That's when all hell broke loose.

The corpse suddenly became bloated, then started spasming. We shot it again, in the head and chest, still nothing. Suddenly, it ripped apart, smearing this red-yellow mixture all over us. It ate through the outer layer of our suits, thankfully stopped about there. Same couldn't be said about our respirators, so we threw them off before they could melt onto our face. As we did, we noticed there was this...thick yellow fog, emerging from the corpse. When we exited the building to get away, it turned out all the bodies did the same. All 32 of them. Soon, we were all breathing these...well, I heard one of the eggheads call them spores.

As I type this from our quarantine facility, I still hear my people complaining about nightmares. Can't blame them. I am not saying we have "PTSD" or other made up crap like that, this was far from the worst thing we've seen. No, these nightmares seem...more vivid, specific. They show us what they want us to believe was everyday life at the settlement, then each dream ends with loud gunfire, screams and our bodies being torn apart by bullets. I assume that whatever we breathed in now forces us to view them.

It is my utmost recommendation that we increase our attacks against KTO-7890-Valentinus. These people are dangerous and willing to fight with any weapons they have, including by disinformation warfare. The faster we deal with them, the better.

//Mundus, Normalis//

Commander Julius Petrić
Strike Team-0984 "Cleaning Crew"
PHYSCIS Division
[[/div]]

[[div class="blockquote"]]
|| **CC:** Operation Sternenfall ||
|| From: ##blue|DBAnna@PHYSICSDiv.goc##||

The following text was found written on a piece of paper inside the temple of the KTO-7890-Valentinus compound. The uneven handwriting, as well as tears in the paper, suggest that it was written in a hurry shortly before or during the Global Occult Coalition's offensive. The author is currently unknown

> This is an official message from the Pan-Nälkä Congress to the Global Occult Coalition.
> 
> We have been preparing ourselves. We were aware another bloodbath was on its way, somewhere and at some point. We have been made aware this would happen shortly before, and we have decided to make sure you will never forget it. Because we won't.
> 
> Many have come after our people in the past. God worshippers, tyrants, witch burners, fascists. We have slaughtered them all.
> 
> This time won't be different. You will shoot us, you will murder us, but as long as a single follower of the Ozi̮rmok remains, we shall achieve our victory.
> 
> Especially now, as we have made some friends. Who do you think alerted us to your attack?
> 
> //May we meet again, under the pink skies//
> 
> //[https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/mundus-liberari Mundus, Liberari]//
> 
> PS: No. These dreams won't end :)

[[/div]]


